post_text: Check out the Summer Food Program through Backus Community Center!
shared_text:
Backus Community Center
May 27 at 2:50 PM ¬∑

SUMMER FOOD SERVICE PROGRAM
Backus Community Center
900 5th Street
International Falls

This program offers free summer meals to children ages 1 to 18, Monday through Friday, June 1 through August 28.

This will be a CARRY OUT service only. Lunches will be picked up daily at the East door of Backus (door #3), between 11:30 a.m. and 1:30 p.m.

Please call Backus to register children. 218-285-7225.

There are no income guidelines or eligibility requirements.

Adults may request a lunch at no charge if they are Food Shelf clients or Servants of Shelter clients.

Backus office hours: Monday - Friday, 7:30 a.m. - 4:00 p.m.

It is Teacher Appreciation Week! There is no better time to show teachers how much you appreciate them than now. Teachers at L-BF, at other schools in our community, and across the nation have been working extra hard to connect with students and provide education through this unprecedented time.
Send teachers a homemade card, an email, or make a yard sign to Thank A Teacher!
Homemade cards can be mailed to the school at:
Littlefork-Big Falls School
700 Main Street
Littlefork, MN 56653
We will get your cards to your teachers for you!

post_text:
Starting this week, WDIO will highlight students in northern Minnesota, Wisconsin and Michigan in their newscasts through the month of May.

The following Littlefork-Big Falls Seniors will be showcased on the following schedule:
Danielle Erickson & Kelly Krause: May 7, 2020 at 10:00 p.m.
Cam McRoberts & McKenzie Swenson: May 11, 2020 at 10:00 p.m.
Sydney Stevens: May 28, 2020 at 5:00 p.m.

The Senior Salute messages will also be posted on the WDIO website and streaming app for anyone who may have missed it in the newscasts.

Again, congratulations on your upcoming graduation. We are proud of you and wish you the very best in your future endeavors.

post_text:
Reminder that there will be No School on Friday, April 10 and Monday, April 13 for our regularly scheduled Easter Break.
What this means in our new atmosphere of distance learning is there will be no attendance taken, no assignments assigned, no food service deliveries or pickup, and no child care. The building will be closed these two days and no staff will be available.
Everyone enjoy the long weekend, FaceTime or Zoom your extended family and friends, and hopefully there will be nice weather to enjoy.
We will begin attendance, assignments, food service, and childcare again on Tuesday, April 14th!

Paul Bunyan Communication in cooperation with the city of Big Falls and the Littlefork-Big Falls School district has installed and activated 2 free WiFi locations in the city of Big Falls, one on the exterior of the Community Building and one on the exterior of the Liquor Store in order to better serve those students and parents that have little or no access to broadband service during the stay at home and distance learning period.
These access points are designed for students and parents to be able to connect to the internet and communicate with their teachers and access course materials.
Social Distancing rules still apply, access to the buildings are not required. If you have any questions about this service please contact Mr. Hand at the Littlefork-Big Falls School District using email hand_f@isd362.k12.mn.us or 218-278-6614 ext 217.

Governor Tim Walz and Education Commissioner Mary Cathryn Ricker have announced that all Minnesota public school districts and charter schools will implement a Distance Learning Period beginning on March 30, 2020, until at least May 4, 2020. *This may be subject to change.*
The L-BF Distance Learning plan will be posted no later than 4:00 p.m. on Friday, March 27.
Stay tuned for a more detailed update tomorrow afternoon!
Thank you to all our very patient L-BF families!

post_text:
In order to clarify expectations for parents and students during the closure beginning today through Friday, March 27th. Please see the following information.

1. The end of 3rd Quarter is this Friday, March 20th. For students who have missing assignments that need to be turned in, all staff are working through the break. Contact teachers by email or phone at the school to make arrangements for missing work.

2. No new assignments or homework is to be assigned during the closure from March 18 - March 27, per state guidelines. 4th Quarter work will begin on March 30th. We will be notifying everyone on how that will look no later than Friday, March 27th per state guidelines.

Please continue to check the school website under Recent News, School Update COVID-19, and our Facebook page for updates as we are able to provide them.

Thank you for your continued patience as we navigate this uncharted territory.

shared_text:
MSHSL
December 9, 2019 at 7:17 PM ¬∑

Littlefork-Big Falls High School knows how to treat officials right and set a great example for fans.

Here's an email sent to the MSHSL by Kyle Lamppa, one of the officials in these photos.

When officiating basketball at Littlefork-Big Falls, they provide "referee helpers" during the game. They are kids ranging from 3rd-5th grade. They are dressed in referee striped shirts with a screen print on the back of "respect the refs." During timeouts, they run onto the floor, bring us water to drink, chat with us, and then head back to the sideline. They are prompt, safe, and really add to the enjoyment of officiating events at the school. The students, their parents, and the administration at the school should be commended for thinking of this gesture and really making our night with it. On long winter nights, officiating multiple games a week, it truly is the "little" gestures that make it worth while. Kudos to Littlefork-Big Falls.

post_text: L-BF is aware of the current situation in International Falls. We are keeping up to date on the situation as it progresses. L-BF is not part of the threat at this time and we are continuing school as normal at this time under closed campus protocol.
shared_text:
The Journal, International Falls MN
November 18, 2019 at 5:28 PM ¬∑

Police Chief Rich Mastin confirmed that the school this morning received information indicating a potential threat against the school.
Both schools have been evacuated and children are being sent to First Lutheran Church, said a school notification. Children will be bused to their normal drop off sites as soon as possible. Parents who choose to pick up their children should use the frontage road to the church, and not 11th Street.
He said the police department and schools are following their plan as a precaution.
A large law enforcement presence is at the school now, and includes the sheriff's office, police, Border Patrol and fire department as a precaution.
ISD 361 students are being evacuated due to a threat that is being investigated, according to Koochiching County Sheriff Perryn Hedlund. No further information is available at this time. Parts of 11th Street are blocked off to restrict access.

post_text: L-BF High School students had the opportunity to attend the first ever 218 Trades Expo in Eveleth, MN this month. The expo features employers, trade unions, and trade schools from around the area offering information to students about future employment opportunities in our area in various trades. Plumbing, carpentry, masonry, and heavy equipment operating were just a few of the trades represented at the expo. See the following link to view WDIO news coverage on the event. post_text:
Littlefork-Big Falls would like to remind our Sports fans that L-BF is a Pet Free facility. There are no pets allowed anywhere on the Premises. Please respect the signs posted.

Administrators are pet owners too and understand the desire to bring your dog to an outdoor event, but we must comply with insurance and state health regulations.

No dogs are allowed anywhere in or around the complex or fields. This includes all common areas and parking lots. If dogs are seen on the premises, owners will be asked to leave the complex immediately and if dogs are present near or around any field the game will be halted until the dog is removed to the parking area, but must be removed permanently from the complex as well.

***Properly marked and leashed service dogs are permitted at the complex..****

Thank you for your cooperation.
